balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

changeAddress(uint256,address).details: Allows token creator to change their address

params._newCreatorAddress: New creator address associated with the token
params._tokenId: ID of the token in question

changeDescription(uint256,string).details: Allows token creator to change the description of their token

params._newDescription: New description associated with the token
params._tokenId: ID of the token in question

changeName(uint256,string).details: Allows token creator to change the name of their token

params._newName: New name associated with the token
params._tokenId: ID of the token in question

changeSymbol(uint256,string).details: Allows token creator to change the symbol of their token

params._newSymbol: New symbol associated with the token
params._tokenId: ID of the token in question

changeVerification(uint256,bool).details: Allows owner to verify (or undo verification) of a CreatorToken

params._tokenId: ID of the token in question
params._verified: Verification status of the token in question

params._creatorAddress: Address of the creator of the token
params._description: chosen by the creator of the tokens
params._name: Name chosen by the creator of the token
params._symbol: Ticker symbol chosen by the creator of the token

getCreatorTokenCount().details: Returns the current length of the creatorTokens array

returns._0: uint representing number of unique Creator Tokens

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Denotes whether operator is approved to transfer account's tokens

params._operator: Wallet address which is/isn't approved to transfer _account's tokens

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

payoutPlatformFees(address).details: Pays out platform fees owed to owner (might opt to call this daily)

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._amounts: Array of quantities of token to be transferred
params._from: Address token is being transferred from
params._ids: Array of IDs of tokens being transferred
params._to: Address token is being transferred to

params._amount: Quantity of token to be transferred
params._from: Address token is being transferred from
params._to: Address token is being transferred to

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Gives operator permission to transfer caller's tokens

params._approved: Boolean value indicating whether operator is approved

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.
